I worked for this really
rich, powerful man,

07:44.899 --> 07:47.554
and he had a team of chefs
in his corporate kitchen,

07:47.597 --> 07:49.251
and I learned a lot
from those guys.

07:49.294 --> 07:50.861
Were they from all
over the world?

07:50.905 --> 07:52.036
Yeah.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.298
From a young age,
I hated school,

07:53.342 --> 07:55.083
and the vice principal
said to me,

07:55.126 --> 07:56.780
"Maybe it's best
if you just drop out."

07:56.824 --> 07:58.608
That's when my mom said,
"You know, as long as

07:58.652 --> 08:00.567
you make the world
your classroom."

08:00.610 --> 08:02.873
So, I dropped out of school
when I was 16,

08:02.917 --> 08:06.224
studied in Mexico learning
traditional Mexican cooking.

08:06.268 --> 08:07.922
I took pastry courses in France.

08:07.965 --> 08:09.576
I went to Thailand

08:09.619 --> 08:11.708
and studied with the top chef
there for a month.

08:11.752 --> 08:13.275
I took courses in Vietnam,

08:13.318 --> 08:16.104
and I really just pursued
my craft my own way.

08:16.147 --> 08:17.975
