because when the first thing
happened with the chef,

12:56.950 --> 12:58.386
I got backup.

12:58.429 --> 13:00.301
She's already getting paid.

13:00.344 --> 13:02.477
She's just sitting in a hotel
when we could put her to work,

13:02.520 --> 13:04.087
and we have an extra bunk.

13:04.131 --> 13:05.915
And it helps you,
because you know,

13:05.959 --> 13:07.264
the deck team are getting
their 12 hours of rest.

13:07.308 --> 13:09.005
That's not happening on my team.

13:09.049 --> 13:10.833
Wanna bring her on?

13:10.877 --> 13:12.443
-Can I think about it?
-Absolutely.

13:12.487 --> 13:14.445
I mean, let me run
it past the girls

13:14.489 --> 13:15.838
to get their thoughts on it.

13:15.882 --> 13:18.145
-Sure.
-I appreciate that.

13:18.188 --> 13:19.450
I don't know how
I feel about this.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.104
I will talk to you soon,
Captain Sandy.

13:21.148 --> 13:22.410
Okay.

13:22.453 --> 13:23.933
Lexi is not really
pulling her weight,

13:23.977 --> 13:25.979
so we can use the
extra hands for sure.

13:26.022 --> 13:29.896
But I don't want to say
anything to her to hurt her,

13:29.939 --> 13:31.811
because from what I've seen,

13:31.854 --> 13:34.074
I don't think Lexi deals
with things in a good way.

13:34.117 --> 13:35.466
I don't want her to rebel.

13:35.510 --> 13:37.338
I just want us to get
through this charter,

13:37.381 --> 13:39.427
which is proving to be the
hardest charter we've been on

13:39.470 --> 13:41.559
so far because
of all this sh--.

13:41.603 --> 13:44.998
It's just... I feel like
it's gonna be a messy road.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.521
-Hello?

13:46.564 --> 13:47.914
Hi.

13:47.957 --> 13:49.480
Hi, do you wanna jump
into the master?

13:50.655 --> 13:52.048
Thank you.

13:53.049 --> 13:54.485
It's my time to shine.

13:54.529 --> 13:56.313
Well, have a nice evening.

13:58.489 --> 13:59.839
-Do you wanna head upstairs?
-Yeah.

13:59.882 --> 14:01.144
-All right.
-Cool, let's go.

14:01.188 --> 14:03.277
Oh, yeah!

14:03.320 --> 14:05.453
Woo!

14:05.496 --> 14:06.541
Look honey, he's got the white
sausage.

14:06.584 --> 14:07.542
That's my favorite!

14:07.585 --> 14:10.980
-Woo!
-Yeah!

14:11.024 --> 14:13.113
Yes, Mzi!

14:13.156 --> 14:14.288
Did anyone order a beer?

14:14.331 --> 14:16.507
-Oh, yeah!
-Yay!

14:16.551 --> 14:18.858
Hey!

14:25.952 --> 14:27.475
It's so much more fun.

14:27.518 --> 14:29.956
Can you, like, surprise me
with a yummy vodka cocktail?

14:29.999 --> 14:32.001
Of course.

14:32.045 --> 14:34.047
Oh, my God, it's so good up
there, they love it.

14:34.090 --> 14:35.875
I have to surprise her with
a yummy vodka cocktail.

14:35.918 --> 14:37.093
Quick, make her a cosmopolitan.

14:37.137 --> 14:38.312
Yeah, that's what
I was thinking.

14:38.355 --> 14:40.227
-Do you know how to make one?
-No.

14:44.013 --> 14:45.319
Yeah.

14:45.362 --> 14:47.538
Triple sec, cranberry juice,
vodka, lime,

14:47.582 --> 14:50.150
and just shake it and serve
it in a martini glass.

14:50.193 --> 14:51.542
Does anyone else need a beer?

14:54.284 --> 14:55.329
I love it.

14:56.373 --> 14:59.463
-Cheers, bitches!
-Oh!

15:01.074 --> 15:03.032
Thank you, you are the best.

15:04.120 --> 15:05.513
How's it going?

15:05.556 --> 15:07.167
Yeah, good, good.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.603
All the decorations have stayed,
which is plus.

15:11.040 --> 15:12.607
Okay, but then I have
to come back down.

15:15.044 --> 15:16.176
-I didn't get an outfit.
-What?

15:16.219 --> 15:17.525
Oh, Captain Sandy!

15:17.568 --> 15:18.918
I love your outfits!

15:18.961 --> 15:20.354
-Woo!
-Captain, my captain!

15:22.922 --> 15:24.358
Yeah, of course.

15:34.585 --> 15:36.370
Yeah, but we... she wants
you up there for a bit.

15:36.413 --> 15:38.415
It's fun.
Honestly, go, it's nice.

15:41.592 --> 15:43.203
I wanna be a part
of the festivities,

15:43.246 --> 15:44.682
but it's an unfair tradeoff.

15:44.726 --> 15:46.380
I did all the cabins' laundry,

15:46.423 --> 15:48.730
and then if I go up there
for Oktoberfest,

15:48.773 --> 15:50.384
now I'm stuck cleaning
up after you guys,

15:50.427 --> 15:52.255
after you've had fun
with the guests.

15:52.299 --> 15:54.388
I'd rather be in cabins,
finish it off.

15:54.431 --> 15:55.606
Thank you.

15:56.651 --> 15:58.566
-Hey!
-Yes!

15:58.609 --> 16:00.002
Look at you!

16:00.046 --> 16:01.264
-Oh, my God.
-Loving it?

16:01.308 --> 16:02.396
Yes.

16:04.398 --> 16:06.356
I'm definitely at a point
where I would prefer

16:06.400 --> 16:08.097
a steady and
healthy relationship,

16:08.141 --> 16:09.881
and obviously with Malia,
it's not gonna happen.

16:13.755 --> 16:15.539
And it's fine, like,
I can live with that,

16:15.583 --> 16:18.107
but the realization that
I am just spooning a pillow,

16:18.151 --> 16:19.979
just feeling sorry for myself

16:20.022 --> 16:21.632
because it's not a human being,

16:21.676 --> 16:23.721
it is what it is, isn't it?

16:23.765 --> 16:26.420
I will see you in a few hours.

16:26.463 --> 16:28.726
-All righty.
-Somebody hold my beer.

16:31.294 --> 16:32.513
We need more people!

16:32.556 --> 16:33.557
Oh, my God.

16:34.689 --> 16:35.646
...but she said no.

16:35.690 --> 16:37.605
Okay.

16:37.648 --> 16:39.781
Everyone's having fun upstairs,
and she's isolating herself.

16:39.824 --> 16:41.652
I don't want her
to feel isolated.

16:41.696 --> 16:43.741
Like, what else can I do?
I'm trying.

16:43.785 --> 16:46.048
-Drink!
-Hey!

16:46.092 --> 16:50.139
Woo!

16:50.183 --> 16:53.751
-Oh, my God!
-Oh!

16:53.795 --> 16:57.146
Attaboy, Mzi!
That's my boy!

16:57.190 --> 17:00.062
I do have some experience in
the beer-drinking department.

17:00.106 --> 17:03.109
We used to host an
annual beer Olympics

17:03.152 --> 17:05.633
at the digs that I used
to live at in Cape Town.

17:05.676 --> 17:08.027
I feel like I'm quite shy
and reserved,

17:08.070 --> 17:12.553
and alcohol can definitely
change that up a little bit.

17:12.596 --> 17:14.729
My friends at home would
be extremely disappointed

17:14.772 --> 17:16.339
in me right now.

17:19.386 --> 17:20.430
Yeah.

17:24.652 --> 17:27.176
How are you feeling after
everything that's happened?

17:27.220 --> 17:28.612
I'm feeling better.

17:28.656 --> 17:31.354
I'm just, like, taking
my time, you know?

17:31.398 --> 17:33.008
You're very quiet,
so I just wanna make sure...

17:33.052 --> 17:34.444
-Oh, yeah, I feel good.
-That you're still...

17:34.488 --> 17:36.011
-I'm good, I'm getting back.
-Okay.

17:36.055 --> 17:37.752
Tomorrow, breakfast will
be set first thing.

17:37.795 --> 17:40.059
Yeah, it just
can't happen again.

17:40.102 --> 17:41.756
There's one other thing.

17:41.799 --> 17:44.063
We had another girl
that quarantined.

17:44.106 --> 17:45.586
Uh-huh?

17:45.629 --> 17:46.804
Basically she's just sitting
there doing nothing.

17:46.848 --> 17:49.111
Okay.

17:49.155 --> 17:52.680
I'm feeling very anxious about
bringing in another person.

17:52.723 --> 17:55.683
Okay.
What's her position?

17:55.726 --> 17:59.165
I don't know her experience,
but I just want you to know

17:59.208 --> 18:00.818
this is not me trying
to replace you...

18:00.862 --> 18:02.168
-Okay.
-After everything.

18:02.211 --> 18:03.386
Because I know how
it can seem...

18:03.430 --> 18:04.561
-Right.
-And how it can look.

18:04.605 --> 18:06.302
And I genuinely mean it,
Lexi, like,

18:06.346 --> 18:07.782
please believe me
when I say that.

18:07.825 --> 18:09.740
-Okay. No, I understand.
-We do have an extra bunk.

18:09.784 --> 18:11.046
We have an extra bed?

18:11.090 --> 18:12.656
In the boys' cabin.

18:12.700 --> 18:14.310
They've got three beds.

18:14.354 --> 18:16.095
Well, I appreciate it.
I'm not offended at all.

18:16.138 --> 18:17.705
Okay, I just...

18:19.185 --> 18:21.143
I think it will help us,

18:21.187 --> 18:22.753
but I am concerned
about the dynamic.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.103
All righty.

18:39.205 --> 18:40.249
-Okay.
-All righty.

18:40.293 --> 18:41.729
-Thank you.
-No problem.

18:41.772 --> 18:42.817
-I'm gonna finish putting up...
-Yeah, yeah.

18:42.860 --> 18:44.123
Crew stuff.

18:45.602 --> 18:47.343
Oh ----ing Chad.

18:47.387 --> 18:49.389
-Yes!
-Woo!

18:51.130 --> 18:52.653
I have the best deck crew.

18:52.696 --> 18:54.176
They're dancing around,

18:54.220 --> 18:56.352
just making absolute
fools of themselves.

18:56.396 --> 18:58.137
Woo!

18:58.180 --> 19:00.269
There's no egos here,
there's no cockiness.

19:00.313 --> 19:02.706
Willkommen zum Oktoberfest!

19:02.750 --> 19:05.405
Best night ever.

19:05.448 --> 19:06.754
Lloyd!

19:09.757 --> 19:12.455
Apparently we had a girl
on standby,

19:12.499 --> 19:15.284
so, that's quarantined,
so because she's sitting

19:15.328 --> 19:17.852
in quarantine doing nothing,
I think we can use the help.

19:17.895 --> 19:19.506
What's she's coming as?

19:19.549 --> 19:20.724
I mean, I don't know,
but I wanna keep her,

19:20.768 --> 19:23.379
like, more down.

19:23.423 --> 19:24.380
I'm not going down to fourth.

19:24.424 --> 19:25.729
You're not, no, no.

19:27.601 --> 19:30.430
Well, that's another thing,
is cabin arrangements.

19:31.953 --> 19:33.563
No, I don't know.

19:33.607 --> 19:34.869
Obviously we need the help,
but we need the help

19:34.912 --> 19:36.697
because Lexi isn't
doing her job.

19:36.740 --> 19:39.569
So, really, she should just
be coming on to replace Lexi.

19:39.613 --> 19:40.788
This is ----ing annoying.

19:43.573 --> 19:44.922
Coming up...

19:44.966 --> 19:46.446
Being business owners,
I just figure, like,

19:46.489 --> 19:50.232
you would want to know
experiences that we had.

19:50.276 --> 19:52.626
We felt like there was
a little lack of attention.

19:57.152 --> 19:58.719
We had a girl on standby.

19:58.762 --> 20:01.112
I think we can use the help.

20:01.156 --> 20:02.679
What is she coming on as?

20:02.723 --> 20:04.290
I mean, I don't know,
but I wanna keep her, like,

20:04.333 --> 20:07.075
more down.

20:07.118 --> 20:08.555
Well, that's another thing,
is cabin arrangements.

20:08.598 --> 20:09.512
You guys missed the dance-off.

20:09.556 --> 20:11.471
Oh, what's going on?

20:11.514 --> 20:16.432
We got a girl in quarantine,
and the boat's paying for her,

20:16.476 --> 20:19.392
so she might come on for
next trip, I don't know.

20:19.435 --> 20:21.263
I think maybe
it's time to go to dinner.

20:21.307 --> 20:22.438
Do you know what time
we're having dinner?

20:22.482 --> 20:23.439
We're actually eating dinner.

20:23.483 --> 20:25.006
I will double-check for you now.

20:25.049 --> 20:26.964
-Should we do beer?
-Sleeping arrangements?

20:27.008 --> 20:29.750
David goes in with the boys, and
then someone goes in with Mat.

20:29.793 --> 20:31.273
Someone goes in with Mat.

20:31.317 --> 20:33.188
Lexi should have to go with Mat.

20:33.232 --> 20:34.407
Just kidding...
don't do that.

20:34.450 --> 20:35.669
No, they do not...

20:35.712 --> 20:37.279
I'm just joking, don't do that.

20:37.323 --> 20:38.324
We'll be back
to three stews and no chef.

20:38.367 --> 20:39.673
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

20:39.716 --> 20:41.631
Katie, what time are
they eating dinner?

20:41.675 --> 20:44.330
Well, apparently 9:00ish, but
I don't know, are they hungry?

20:44.373 --> 20:45.679
They would like to know.

20:45.722 --> 20:47.376
He's not gonna be...

20:50.161 --> 20:51.075
<i>Galley.</i>

20:51.119 --> 20:52.947
How long do you need for dinner?

20:52.990 --> 20:53.948
<i>-Twenty minutes.</i>
-Okay.

20:53.991 --> 20:55.428
<i>You want me to go in 20,</i>

20:55.471 --> 20:57.212
<i>or are you gonna call me
when the guests--</i>

20:57.256 --> 20:58.561
No, they were just asking
so I'm just making sure.

20:58.605 --> 21:00.259
<i>-Katie, I love you.</i>
-Bye.

21:04.437 --> 21:05.786
You guys are hungry?

21:05.829 --> 21:07.309
We're ready whenever
you guys are.

21:07.353 --> 21:09.137
So, Cheffy needs 20 minutes.

21:09.180 --> 21:11.444
If he's good at, like, 8:35?

21:11.487 --> 21:13.489
8:35 is good for everybody?

21:13.533 --> 21:15.665
-Yeah.
-Perfect.

21:17.537 --> 21:20.191
I will say this...
smells like God is cooking.

21:22.498 --> 21:24.457
-Galley.
-Hello, Galley.

21:24.500 --> 21:27.155
-What up, baby?
-Be ready for 8:35?

21:27.198 --> 21:28.199
-Cool, bye.
-Bye.

21:28.243 --> 21:30.463
The plans are always changing.

21:30.506 --> 21:32.334
You just gotta roll with it.

21:32.378 --> 21:34.597
When we get to dinner, have it
be, like, a real badass dinner.

21:34.641 --> 21:35.685
Okay.

21:35.729 --> 21:37.470
-Instead of German food.
-Yes!

21:37.513 --> 21:39.298
It's a huge compliment
when someone loves your food

21:39.341 --> 21:41.038
so much that they want you
to keep doing your thing.

21:41.082 --> 21:42.301
When people give
me that feedback,

21:42.344 --> 21:44.085
I really wanna crush it.

21:44.128 --> 21:48.045
Potato gratin, Matatouille,
and rack of lamb persillade.

21:48.089 --> 21:50.265
Mzi, if you want to,
you can go down now.

21:52.093 --> 21:53.224
-Ooh!
-Thank you.

21:53.268 --> 21:54.487
Ooh, lamb lollipops.

21:54.530 --> 21:56.576
So, for your main course tonight

21:56.619 --> 22:00.188
you have a potato gratin
with ratatouille

22:00.231 --> 22:01.407
and a New Zealand rack of lamb.

22:01.450 --> 22:02.408
Ooh, thank you.

22:02.451 --> 22:04.366
Looks amazing.

22:04.410 --> 22:06.150
I think that's how you have
to eat it, it's a lollipop.

22:06.194 --> 22:07.369
Oh, my God.

22:07.413 --> 22:08.501
You're supposed
to hold the bone.

22:08.544 --> 22:09.545
This is so good.

22:11.373 --> 22:12.679
Thanks.

22:12.722 --> 22:14.507
If you wanna get some
extra sleep, you can.

22:14.550 --> 22:15.638
Oh, my God, yeah.

22:15.682 --> 22:16.726
Are those scalloped potatoes?

22:16.770 --> 22:18.337
That's crazy good.

22:20.817 --> 22:22.471
-All right, bye.
-Bye.

22:22.515 --> 22:24.343
Great, okay, wait till
you see my tattoo.

22:24.386 --> 22:27.650
-Oh, God.
-What... I know!

22:27.694 --> 22:29.478
She just scared herself.

22:29.522 --> 22:31.567
Apparently we had sex in
our bathroom that night.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.439
Oh!

22:37.399 --> 22:39.053
That might be a win
for the boys.

22:42.491 --> 22:45.102
-Ah!
-Oh.

22:47.670 --> 22:49.629
-Can I start brûléeing?
-You may.

22:49.672 --> 22:51.326
You're coming up
with the last two.

22:51.370 --> 22:52.501
Why?
Do I make them horny?

22:52.545 --> 22:54.242
You do.

22:54.285 --> 22:55.548
You know we might be getting
a fourth stew, right?

22:55.591 --> 22:57.114
Yeah?

22:57.158 --> 23:00.204
-She might be your cabin mate.
yeah.

23:00.248 --> 23:02.685
Oh, great ----ing timing!

23:02.729 --> 23:04.383
-Yes, sir!
-My man! Woo!

23:04.426 --> 23:06.385
That's vanilla crème brûlée.

23:06.428 --> 23:07.516
We all wanna take you home.

23:07.560 --> 23:08.691
I'm ready to go.

23:08.735 --> 23:09.866
Mat, you've been spot-on.

23:09.910 --> 23:11.607
-Okay.
-Thank you very much.

23:11.651 --> 23:12.608
This is the best crème
brûlée I've ever had.

23:12.652 --> 23:14.218
-Yes.
-Oh, awesome.

23:14.262 --> 23:15.219
-Crème brûlée is my favorite.
-Ooh!

23:15.263 --> 23:16.220
Oh, my gosh.

23:16.264 --> 23:17.221
-Is it good?
-Yeah.

23:17.265 --> 23:19.310
Oh... huh, "is it good."

23:19.354 --> 23:21.138
What's going down?

23:31.497 --> 23:33.194
I don't wanna go to bed.

23:33.237 --> 23:34.630
We'll sleep when we're dead.

23:36.502 --> 23:38.547
-All right. Let's go.
-Perfect.

23:38.591 --> 23:40.506
This is a lot of stairs.

23:40.549 --> 23:42.464
I'm not gonna lie, babe, I'm not
gonna last too much longer.

23:42.508 --> 23:43.639
Okay, good night.

23:48.905 --> 23:49.863
-You good?
-Yeah.

23:49.906 --> 23:50.907
-Cool.
-Thank you.

23:50.951 --> 23:52.300
Thanks, chica.

24:06.314 --> 24:07.271
Good morning.

24:07.315 --> 24:08.272
Morning.

24:08.316 --> 24:09.273
How was your night?

24:09.317 --> 24:10.318
Yeah, good.

24:11.667 --> 24:13.234
Oh, my God.

24:13.277 --> 24:15.671
Hey, Lloyd, we're gonna
need the fenders,

24:15.715 --> 24:18.152
because I'm gonna get ready
to go into the marina.

24:20.502 --> 24:22.809
We're gonna need everybody.

24:22.852 --> 24:24.767
We're gonna need
all hands on deck.

24:24.811 --> 24:27.553
We have to haul anchor and
head right back to the dock.

24:38.346 --> 24:39.303
Wind's picking up already, huh?

24:39.347 --> 24:41.175
Oh, hell, yeah.

24:41.218 --> 24:42.306
I had the guys prep everything
last night, so we're ready.

24:42.350 --> 24:43.656
-Oh.
-On top of it.

24:45.832 --> 24:47.660
Captain Sandy, good morning,
we are hauling.

24:50.837 --> 24:52.534
-Anchor in the pocket.
-Thank you.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.493
What height do you
want the fenders?

24:54.536 --> 24:55.668
Just at the red rail.

24:55.711 --> 24:57.321
Red rail, yeah.

24:57.365 --> 24:59.323
Please just double-check
all your heaving lines.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.804
that's hot,
Jesus.

25:01.848 --> 25:04.154
All right, we can
throw fenders over.

25:07.375 --> 25:08.681
Laundry, great.

25:14.687 --> 25:17.690
Okay, all clear
to start swinging.

25:17.733 --> 25:19.343
Hundred feet to dolphin.

25:19.387 --> 25:20.431
Holy sh--.

25:20.475 --> 25:21.520
Dang.

25:21.563 --> 25:22.912
The current's wicked.

25:24.871 --> 25:26.960
----ing currents.

25:27.003 --> 25:28.396
Incredible.

25:28.439 --> 25:30.398
Port dolphin
approaching midships.

25:31.921 --> 25:33.357
<i>Dave, hurry?</i>

25:33.401 --> 25:34.794
<i>All port lines running now.</i>

25:34.837 --> 25:38.275
Okay, Captain Sandy,
we have 25 feet to the dock.

25:40.277 --> 25:41.278
Oops.

25:42.932 --> 25:44.325
We have tension in port dolphin.

25:44.368 --> 25:46.370
Okay, lock it off there.

25:46.414 --> 25:48.329
<i>-Nice work, everyone.</i>
-Yah.

25:48.372 --> 25:50.374
That was not easy.

25:50.418 --> 25:51.811
-Nice docking.
-Thank you.

25:51.854 --> 25:52.899
It's getting easier, isn't it?

25:52.942 --> 25:54.596
-Yeah, it is.
-Killing it.

25:57.512 --> 25:58.557
I guess.

26:04.432 --> 26:05.999
So, two more minutes.

26:06.042 --> 26:07.261
Is this empty?

26:09.524 --> 26:10.743
Hello?

26:12.440 --> 26:13.702
Do you want anything?

26:13.746 --> 26:15.704
-Well, since you're doing it...
-Yeah?

26:15.748 --> 26:17.619
Here we go, wham, bam,
thank you, ma'am.

26:19.621 --> 26:20.579
Can I get you anything else?

26:20.622 --> 26:21.710
I'm good for the moment.

26:21.754 --> 26:23.494
-Hello.
-Hi.

26:23.538 --> 26:24.713
No guests are up.

26:24.757 --> 26:25.758
There's so much pulp.
Look at that...

26:25.801 --> 26:26.759
it's, like, not moving.

26:26.802 --> 26:27.803
It's like a lava lamp.

26:29.283 --> 26:30.589
I know, right?

26:34.462 --> 26:35.637
Good morning, sunshine.

26:35.681 --> 26:37.552
Oh, good morning, everybody.

26:37.596 --> 26:38.901
Don't be mad at me,
but I made my own drink.

26:38.945 --> 26:39.989
That's fine.

26:40.033 --> 26:41.687
Sorry, I couldn't find you.

26:41.730 --> 26:43.906
Joke's on me, because I
got the very pulpy OJ, so...

26:43.950 --> 26:45.604
There you go,
you should have waited.

26:45.647 --> 26:46.605
I should have.

26:47.649 --> 26:48.955
Or yelled louder.

26:50.434 --> 26:51.740
One thing after another
at this point.

26:51.784 --> 26:53.307
It's obviously clear
to the guests

26:53.350 --> 26:54.438
that we're failing in our job.

26:54.482 --> 26:55.962
Would anyone like a coffee?

26:56.005 --> 26:56.963
You have my tea-maker
back there, right?

26:57.006 --> 26:58.747
Yes, we do, yes.

26:58.791 --> 27:00.836
I go upstairs, and the primary's
pouring his own drink...

27:00.880 --> 27:03.491
super ----ing unacceptable.

27:03.534 --> 27:05.449
Because you were downstairs when
you should have been upstairs,

27:05.493 --> 27:07.930
yet you told me that there
were no guests upstairs,

27:07.974 --> 27:10.454
and that's why you
were downstairs.

27:10.498 --> 27:11.455
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

27:11.499 --> 27:12.456
You're welcome.

27:12.500 --> 27:13.893
Would anyone else like a coffee?

27:13.936 --> 27:15.677
No.

27:17.940 --> 27:19.681
-How you doing?
-Good, how are you?

27:19.725 --> 27:21.640
<i>-Galley.</i>

27:21.683 --> 27:23.424
All right, thank you.

27:23.467 --> 27:25.339
Okay, I'm gonna finish
this scone I was nibbling on.

27:26.688 --> 27:28.908
Oh, something smells
so good in there.

27:28.951 --> 27:30.083
It's my swagger.

27:30.126 --> 27:31.650
Are you doing lobster bennie?

27:31.693 --> 27:32.651
Yeah, two ways.

27:32.694 --> 27:33.956
That looks phenomenal.

27:34.000 --> 27:35.131
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

27:35.175 --> 27:36.655
Did you guys have
fun last night?

27:36.698 --> 27:38.482
-Yeah.
-We had a lot of fun.

27:38.526 --> 27:39.483
From what we remember.

27:39.527 --> 27:40.789
Yeah, the crew was awesome.

27:40.833 --> 27:42.095
How was the chef?
Like, how was his food?

27:42.138 --> 27:43.618
-Oh, my gosh. Unreal.
-Oh, my God.

27:43.662 --> 27:44.706
I know why he's smiling
all the time.

27:44.750 --> 27:46.665
-He's incredible.
-Yeah.

27:46.708 --> 27:48.362
If I was that good of a chef,
I'd smile all the time, too.

27:48.405 --> 27:49.668
-There wasn't one bad thing.
-He has one meal left.

27:49.711 --> 27:50.756
I wonder if he can
blow it with eggs?

27:52.583 --> 27:54.498
Just say "corner" when
you're walking up the stairs,

27:54.542 --> 27:55.978
to make sure no one hits you
and drops that, all right?

27:56.022 --> 27:57.023
-Yeah.
-Corner.

27:57.066 --> 27:58.677
Is this the lobster Benedict?

28:00.853 --> 28:02.028
Thank you.

28:03.420 --> 28:04.378
Lobster Benedict.

28:04.421 --> 28:05.640
-Ooh!
-Oh, wow.

28:05.684 --> 28:06.946
-Oh, my gosh.
-Yeah, that'll do.

28:06.989 --> 28:07.947
-That's a go.
-Yeah.

28:07.990 --> 28:08.948
Appreciate it.

28:08.991 --> 28:10.123
Corner!

28:10.166 --> 28:11.341
And we have a ham Benedict
as well.

28:11.385 --> 28:12.473
-Mathew?
-Yes?

28:12.516 --> 28:13.604
They were singing your praise.

28:13.648 --> 28:15.519
Were they?
That's good.

28:15.563 --> 28:18.871
I guess I can't say I don't
like eggs Benedict anymore.

28:18.914 --> 28:20.829
Should I butter the toast, or
do you have it on the table?

28:20.873 --> 28:22.613
-It's on the table.
-Of course it is, Katie.

28:22.657 --> 28:24.093
Perfection's her charm.

28:24.137 --> 28:25.573
-Are we doing a shot, or what?
-Yeah, ready?

28:25.616 --> 28:26.879
-Cheers to a good week.
-Cheers!

28:26.922 --> 28:28.141
-Yes, cheers.
-And friends.

28:28.184 --> 28:29.533
I feel like I gotta go pack.

28:29.577 --> 28:30.752
Has everyone else
already started?

28:30.796 --> 28:31.753
Yeah, I think
I'm gonna head down.

28:31.797 --> 28:33.059
Lexi, Lexi, Katie.

28:33.102 --> 28:35.061
Do you wanna come help me
clear breakfast?

28:35.104 --> 28:36.715
Copy.

28:38.891 --> 28:41.154
Ugh!
It's so heavy.

28:41.197 --> 28:43.373
Vacation over.

28:43.417 --> 28:44.853
They already finished
eating everything.

28:44.897 --> 28:46.812
All crew, all crew,
please get into your whites

28:46.855 --> 28:49.510
and let's meet on the dock
in five minutes.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.077
Lloyd, let's do this.

28:55.777 --> 28:57.387
Get in there, Mzi.

28:59.128 --> 29:00.434
Just four Chads, hanging out.

29:00.477 --> 29:01.522
Hey, you.

29:01.565 --> 29:04.003
Come on, come on, boy.

29:04.046 --> 29:05.047
On the line.

29:05.091 --> 29:07.833
I meant to say "on the wall."

29:07.876 --> 29:09.095
Thank you.

29:10.183 --> 29:11.532
Oh, wait... reposition.

29:11.575 --> 29:12.707
Wait, I gotta be
able to, like...

29:12.751 --> 29:13.752
Can I hug you?

29:13.795 --> 29:15.797
Yeah, of course you can.

29:15.841 --> 29:16.842
-So fun.
-Lovely to meet you too.

29:16.885 --> 29:18.408
Aw, thank you.

29:19.583 --> 29:22.717
Bye!
Thank you.

29:22.761 --> 29:24.414
I'm so glad you guys
could party with us.

29:24.458 --> 29:25.807
-Thanks for everything.
-You're welcome.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.069
-Appreciate it.
-Thanks for chartering.

29:27.113 --> 29:29.855
Yes, thanks again
for an amazing trip.

29:29.898 --> 29:31.857
This was our second time
doing something like this

29:31.900 --> 29:33.119
with you, Sandy, and
it turned out great.

29:33.162 --> 29:35.861
But being business owners,

29:35.904 --> 29:39.560
I just figured, like, you would
want to know experiences

29:39.603 --> 29:43.825
that we had that we think we
could maybe improve on a little.

29:43.869 --> 29:45.784
We felt like there was a little
lack of attention for us.

29:45.827 --> 29:47.655
I actually had to make
my own drink this morning.

29:47.698 --> 29:50.745
They're not wrong.
There were ups.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.660
I'm livid right now.

29:55.619 --> 29:58.535
I felt like there was
a little lack of attention.

29:58.579 --> 29:59.798
I actually had to make my
own drink this morning.

29:59.841 --> 30:01.103
I don't wanna be negative...

30:01.147 --> 30:02.801
Oh, no, you're...
honestly, thank you.

30:02.844 --> 30:05.804
Your saving grace
is right there.

30:05.847 --> 30:07.022
Mat's food was ridiculous.

30:07.066 --> 30:08.023
We're gonna kidnap him.

30:08.067 --> 30:09.720
It was amazing.

30:09.764 --> 30:11.592
Deck crew, you guys are badass.
You took care of us.

30:11.635 --> 30:12.680
There were just those
moments where it felt

30:12.723 --> 30:13.724
like I couldn't find anybody.

30:13.768 --> 30:14.813
Thanks for the feedback.

30:14.856 --> 30:16.031
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

30:16.075 --> 30:17.032
-Yeah.
-Here's for the best part.

30:17.076 --> 30:18.033
Awesome, awesome.

30:18.077 --> 30:19.513
There you go.

30:19.556 --> 30:20.688
Ugh, it's so heavy...
thank you.

30:20.731 --> 30:21.689
-Thank you, guys.
-Thank you.

30:21.732 --> 30:23.125
Bye.

30:23.169 --> 30:25.127
Let's get out of our whites,
into our reds,

30:25.171 --> 30:26.650
and meet in the main salon
for our tip meeting.

30:26.694 --> 30:28.130
-Woo!
-Cool.

30:28.174 --> 30:30.045
-Nice job.
-Thank you.

30:32.613 --> 30:33.701
No, you know what...

30:35.834 --> 30:38.097
Katie, what did he mean that he
had no one to mix him a drink?

30:38.140 --> 30:40.708
This morning when I came up,
they were all up.

30:40.751 --> 30:41.970
Oh.

30:45.931 --> 30:48.977
To be pinpointed
out of the whole crew

30:49.021 --> 30:50.849
that your department is failing,

30:50.892 --> 30:53.329
and it really comes
down to one person.

30:53.373 --> 30:56.680
If one of my stews up,
it comes to me.

30:56.724 --> 30:58.247
Oh, my God.

30:58.291 --> 31:00.249
Captain Sandy's gonna think
I'm a ----ing idiot

31:00.293 --> 31:02.251
if I don't accept
the extra help.

31:02.295 --> 31:03.905
I feel like
my hands are tied.

31:03.949 --> 31:05.167
Shall we talk a second?

31:05.211 --> 31:08.867
Okay... uh-oh.

31:08.910 --> 31:13.001
Um, my gut's telling me no,
but she's here.

31:13.045 --> 31:16.700
We've been paying her,
I can use the help.

31:16.744 --> 31:18.964
I don't want another complaint
like I had last charter.

31:19.007 --> 31:21.009
We might as well try,
and if it doesn't work,

31:21.053 --> 31:22.010
it doesn't work.

31:22.054 --> 31:23.142
Great.

31:23.185 --> 31:24.143
-Four days to...
-Yeah.

31:24.186 --> 31:26.536
-...have a shot.
-Okay.

31:26.580 --> 31:30.192
-If there's anything...
-Then whatever you need.

31:30.236 --> 31:31.977
Allowing Katie to
make that decision

31:32.020 --> 31:35.197
is about her seeing
that I believe in her.

31:35.241 --> 31:37.025
She's been a chief stew
for a long time.

31:37.069 --> 31:38.897
She's had eight girls under her.

31:38.940 --> 31:40.724
Like, she's got this.

31:40.768 --> 31:42.770
-Okay, thank you.
-You're welcome.

31:45.251 --> 31:47.731
<i>All crew, all crew,
meet in the main salon</i>

31:47.775 --> 31:49.081
<i>for our tip meeting.</i>

31:49.124 --> 31:51.213
Opa!

31:51.257 --> 31:52.911
Thank you, darling.

31:52.954 --> 31:55.914
So, I mean,
we're mid-charter season,

31:55.957 --> 31:58.133
we had our first complaint.

31:58.177 --> 32:00.875
I like to call this
constructive criticism.

32:00.919 --> 32:02.746
As a business owner,

32:02.790 --> 32:05.706
he highlighted the things that
we really need to improve on.

32:05.749 --> 32:08.013
So, we wanna bring
that energy back up.

32:08.056 --> 32:09.928
I'm adding someone.

32:09.971 --> 32:13.235
She is a deck stew, but she's
coming out to help interior.

32:13.279 --> 32:15.803
This is not a person
to replace anybody,

32:15.846 --> 32:17.109
this is someone to support us.

32:17.152 --> 32:18.937
I ----ing hate this.

32:29.904 --> 32:31.079
Who's she rooming with?

32:31.123 --> 32:32.428
I think she should
go in with Mat.

32:32.472 --> 32:33.952
Dave, come in with us.

32:33.995 --> 32:35.257
Yeah, is that okay
with you guys?

32:35.301 --> 32:36.955
-Yeah.
-Thank you for that.

32:36.998 --> 32:39.392
I'm excited, because
it might be quite nice

32:39.435 --> 32:42.221
to kind of have a bit more
conversation with the lads.

32:42.264 --> 32:45.659
But at the same time, it's
three bodies in a small room.

32:45.702 --> 32:47.139
There's not a lot of space,

32:47.182 --> 32:50.142
and I try to keep things
as clean as I possibly can.

32:50.185 --> 32:53.754
It might jib on me a little bit
if it's ----ing chaos in there.

32:53.797 --> 32:59.238
Mat, I've never heard one
complaint about your food, ever.

32:59.281 --> 33:00.369
Thank you for that.

33:00.413 --> 33:01.936
You're welcome, thank you.

33:01.980 --> 33:05.026
Even though we had our
constructive criticism,

33:05.070 --> 33:06.941
it's the biggest tip
this season.

33:06.985 --> 33:08.073
Woo!

33:08.116 --> 33:12.120
So, we got $23,585,

33:12.164 --> 33:15.819
and it's $1,965 per person,

33:15.863 --> 33:17.821
1,658 euros per person.

33:17.865 --> 33:18.997
Woo!

33:19.040 --> 33:20.781
Yo, my food
was great this charter.

33:20.824 --> 33:22.870
I was the saving grace, biggest
tip of the season so far,

33:22.913 --> 33:24.350
and I hope they all
keep getting bigger.

33:24.393 --> 33:26.961
-Where are you going?
-I'm gonna wash dishes.

33:27.005 --> 33:28.702
We've all got beds to make too.

33:28.745 --> 33:30.878
Katie, watch the crack.

33:30.921 --> 33:32.314
Dave, come in with us.

33:32.358 --> 33:34.099
So, I was...
yeah, I think that's the best.

33:34.142 --> 33:35.404
I think it works, Mat and her.

33:35.448 --> 33:36.797
Yeah, it makes more sense.

33:36.840 --> 33:38.320
As long as... yeah.

33:38.364 --> 33:41.019
You just have to tell her,
like, we only have a coed cabin.

33:41.062 --> 33:42.977
Yeah.

33:43.021 --> 33:45.980
Plus, there's a lot of room in
that cabin as well, with Mat.

33:46.024 --> 33:47.416
Plus, she hasn't met Mat yet,
so she'll be fine with it.

33:47.460 --> 33:49.157
Oh, Jesus.

33:53.248 --> 33:55.294
No, Katie's just
doing the pantries.

33:55.337 --> 33:58.079
Okay, I'll start in the master.

33:58.123 --> 34:00.212
What do we think about
having another stew?

34:00.255 --> 34:02.910
It could be quite interesting
to see if the dynamic changes.

34:02.953 --> 34:03.911
Thanks for being the best.

34:05.434 --> 34:07.175
Sweet, I'd better clean
up my sh--.

34:07.219 --> 34:08.829
You better.

34:08.872 --> 34:11.136
Mathew, Katie, Malia,
meet me in the crew mess

34:11.179 --> 34:13.138
for charter number five
preference sheet meeting.

34:13.181 --> 34:14.791
Roger-dodger.

34:19.361 --> 34:20.319
Oh sh--.

34:20.362 --> 34:21.407
-Ooh!
-Mm-hmm.

34:21.450 --> 34:22.408
-Oh!
-All lay-days!

34:22.451 --> 34:24.192
Ladies.

34:24.236 --> 34:27.195
Best friends Niki and Halie
are true Southern belles.

34:27.239 --> 34:30.720
Niki is a well-known realtor and
Halie owns a clothing boutique.

34:30.764 --> 34:32.896
Joining Niki and Halie are
their friends

34:32.940 --> 34:34.898
Krystal, Sarah, Ashley,

34:34.942 --> 34:36.335
Andrea, realtor,

34:36.378 --> 34:39.120
Bailey, an influencer,
and Danielle, a housewife.

34:39.164 --> 34:42.950
"Niki Wiley eats like a
five-year-old," that's so cute.

34:42.993 --> 34:45.126
She likes bacon, bacon,
and more bacon,

34:45.170 --> 34:46.954
French toast or pancakes.

34:46.997 --> 34:48.216
Sushi!

34:48.260 --> 34:50.044
Halie does not eat like
a five-year-old.

34:50.088 --> 34:51.872
Dairy allergy, don't eat corn,

34:51.915 --> 34:54.875
gluten-free or high-carb,
eat dairy-free keto.

34:54.918 --> 34:56.355
What the is that?

34:56.398 --> 35:00.359
Wow, this might be our
most dietary restrictions...

35:00.402 --> 35:02.883
not my favorite.

35:02.926 --> 35:04.537
At least one of them eats
like a five-year-old,

35:04.580 --> 35:05.538
so that will be easy.

35:05.581 --> 35:07.105
But this is ----ing intense.

35:07.148 --> 35:09.194
There's all sorts
of dietary restrictions,

35:09.237 --> 35:10.891
it's all girls.

35:10.934 --> 35:12.501
You know they're gonna
be high maintenance.

35:12.545 --> 35:14.460
All of the guests
would like a beach picnic.

35:14.503 --> 35:16.897
-Ugh.
-Lovely.

35:16.940 --> 35:18.072
Thank you, everybody.

35:18.116 --> 35:20.292
You guys enjoy your evening.

35:20.335 --> 35:22.294
Oh, God, I'm so tired.

35:27.473 --> 35:28.778
-Okay, shots?
-Yeah.

35:28.822 --> 35:30.128
Let's get it.

35:30.171 --> 35:32.434
What would you girls like?

35:32.478 --> 35:35.394
So, now you wanna be
a bartender?

35:35.437 --> 35:37.396
Lexi, less sass. Just...

35:37.439 --> 35:39.833
Okay.
Okay.

35:43.315 --> 35:45.055
I feel like once
you've had a shot,

35:45.099 --> 35:47.797
you'll be, like, less sass queen
and more yas queen.

35:47.841 --> 35:49.277
Okay, or it could
turn it up a notch.

35:49.321 --> 35:52.237
You want sassy queen
or chill queen?

35:52.280 --> 35:54.804
Sass!

36:06.990 --> 36:08.383
Are you gonna come now?

36:08.427 --> 36:10.124
Yeah, I was just gonna
stretch for a little bit.

36:12.170 --> 36:15.216
Yeah.

36:15.260 --> 36:17.131
-Hello.
-Hello.

36:18.480 --> 36:20.439
How are you feeling
on the interior?

36:31.537 --> 36:33.452
-Was that this morning?
-Yeah.

36:33.495 --> 36:35.149
That sucks, because
then it reflects on,

36:35.193 --> 36:37.586
-like, the whole team.
-Yeah.

36:37.630 --> 36:39.284
And that reflects on
Katie, when Katie's been,

36:39.327 --> 36:40.589
like, busting her ass.

36:42.025 --> 36:43.462
Hopefully good for you guys.

36:43.505 --> 36:45.290
It depends on her personality,
I think, because

36:45.333 --> 36:47.466
there's some people that can
rock in mid-charter season

36:47.509 --> 36:49.032
and, like, kill it.

36:55.865 --> 36:57.867
I haven't done much
stretching, though.

37:03.308 --> 37:04.831
I'm going straight to bed.

37:11.272 --> 37:12.491
Top of the morning to you.

37:12.534 --> 37:14.101
Top of the morning to you, bro.

37:14.144 --> 37:15.494
Hi, boys.

37:15.537 --> 37:16.669
Hey, you wanna join us?

37:16.712 --> 37:17.670
I'm bored.

37:17.713 --> 37:19.498
You hot-tubbing?

37:19.541 --> 37:21.543
I feel a bit of trauma as
Lexi's walking up the stairs.

37:30.335 --> 37:32.032
I feel like Lexi is just
sort of just a bit

37:32.075 --> 37:33.163
of a ticking time bomb,

37:33.207 --> 37:34.904
waiting for it to
happen again.

37:34.948 --> 37:36.297
I'm just watching you guys.

37:38.038 --> 37:41.041
Coming up, a sneak peek
at what's ahead this season.

37:41.084 --> 37:42.564
Yeah.

37:42.608 --> 37:45.654
His blood pressure is
really high, he has chest pains.

37:45.698 --> 37:47.221
-It was my responsibility.
-I don't trust you.

37:47.265 --> 37:48.353
I don't trust you.

37:51.747 --> 37:53.358
Hi, boys.

37:53.401 --> 37:54.533
Hey, you wanna join us?
Hot-tubbing?

37:54.576 --> 37:55.621
We're having a grand old time.

37:55.664 --> 37:57.057
Come and join us in the pool.

37:57.100 --> 37:58.928
Okay, I'm coming back, boys.

38:04.630 --> 38:07.110
Everyone's asleep,
they're boring.

38:09.156 --> 38:10.592
-Hello? <i>
-Hi. Did you ring?</i>

38:10.636 --> 38:13.987
I've been trying to call
you to say happy birthday.

38:14.030 --> 38:15.249
<i>That's all right,
love, don't worry.</i>

38:15.293 --> 38:17.425
-This is nice.
-Yeah.

38:23.475 --> 38:24.650
-Why?
-You haven't?

38:24.693 --> 38:25.694
Well, I wasn't allowed as a kid.

38:25.738 --> 38:26.695
-Oh, really?
-Oh.

38:26.739 --> 38:28.088
Okay.

38:28.131 --> 38:29.263
Yeah, my mom was
one of those moms.

38:29.307 --> 38:30.308
-Yeah.
-I'm going to ask...

38:30.351 --> 38:31.700
On what grounds is it banned?

38:31.744 --> 38:32.701
Because it's witchcraft,
so it's, like,

38:32.745 --> 38:34.747
it was against my religion.

38:34.790 --> 38:37.489
Both of my parents were
super religious, and so, like,

38:37.532 --> 38:40.970
when I got to college,
